FBIS4-776 "drafr073_c_94019" FBIS-AFR-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Situation in Bophuthatswana Said Worsening Situation in Bophuthatswana Said Worsening MB1404161494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 14 Apr 94 MB1404161494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The situation in Bophuthatswana is reported to be on the brink of going out of control. A co-administrator of the homeland, Mr. Job Mokgoro, said after a meeting with the Bophuthatswana police in Mmabatho that law and order was threatened and that this could affect the elections in the territory. Mr. Mokgoro said the TEC [Transitional Executive Council] had been informed of the deteriorating situation in the homeland. Reacting to rumors that certain police members loyal to the deposed government were regrouping to disrupt the election in the homeland. He said the police were investigating the situation.
